---
/**
 * src/pages/index.astro — redirects / → /blog/
 *
 * This file handles the root URL of the blog project.
 * Rather than a blank page, it immediately redirects visitors to /blog/.
 *
 * Why redirect instead of putting content here?
 * The blog URL structure centers on /blog/ — all routes, the sitemap,
 * and links from the main site all point there. Having content at the root
 * would create a duplicate page and confuse the site structure.
 */
---
<meta http-equiv="refresh" content="0; url=/blog/" />
<link rel="canonical" href="/blog/" />
<p>Redirecting to <a href="/blog/">Signals &amp; Sensemaking</a>...</p>
